title: Washington-Rochambeau National Historic Trail: Delaware
body: Explore This Park    Plan Your Visit     Places To Go     Delaware              Delaware - Places To Go           Hale-Byrnes House Hale-Byrnes House image  Hale-Byrnes House Built around 1750, this house was used by General Washington for a war council to discuss the defense of Philadelphia in September 1777.  Today it serves as one of many historical sites connected to the trail.
